Description: Convex ring foot and floor sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery skyphos (?); surface of floor inside lost. Inside and outside of foot glazed; stand-ring and underside reserved. Inscription cut on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 540)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1276)
